383
00:35:48,528 --> 00:35:51,361
- 你好！
- 你是在撒谎吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Howdy!
- Were you fibbing about that?{\r}

384
00:35:51,531 --> 00:35:53,328
- 不是
- 完全不是
{\fscx70\fscy70}- No.
- Not at all.{\r}

385
00:35:54,868 --> 00:35:56,563
你不该偷看的，迪克
{\fscx70\fscy70}You're not supposed to peek, Dick.{\r}

386
00:35:56,736 --> 00:35:59,170
是啊，不过你这么漂亮
我真的无法把持
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, you're just so pretty
I can't help myself.{\r}

387
00:35:59,339 --> 00:36:01,830
- 这事你得警告他
- 你们好
{\fscx70\fscy70}- You need to be warning him about that.
- Howdy.{\r}

388
00:36:02,008 --> 00:36:05,944
应该关心的是地里的庄稼
也应该关心关心工作…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Worry about the field instead,
might be able to worry about the work...{\r}

389
00:36:06,112 --> 00:36:07,977
你们好！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Howdy!{\r}

390
00:36:08,748 --> 00:36:11,717
- 终于到家了
- 我很高兴，鲍勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Finally home.
- I'm so glad, Bob.{\r}

391
00:36:11,885 --> 00:36:14,547
我也住那个房间，鲍勃
别把我的东西弄乱了
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm in that room too, Bob.
Don't mess with my things.{\r}

392
00:36:14,721 --> 00:36:16,746
好的，爷爷
{\fscx70\fscy70}All right, Grandpa.{\r}

393
00:36:22,562 --> 00:36:28,159
“7月9日
勤奋，机智，强烈的责任感…
{\fscx70\fscy70}"July 9th. Diligence, tact,
and a keen sense of responsibility...{\r}

394
00:36:28,334 --> 00:36:32,737
…细致入微，这些都是你的强项
你很敬业”
{\fscx70\fscy70}...capacity for detail are your dominant
traits. Your sense of duty's strong."{\r}

395
00:37:17,050 --> 00:37:18,677
你在这多久了？
{\fscx70\fscy70}How long you been there?{\r}

396
00:37:18,852 --> 00:37:21,753
刚来，错过了很多好看的东西吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Just now arrived. Did I miss much?{\r}

397
00:37:23,490 --> 00:37:26,926
如果你从没见过一个肮脏的男人洗澡
那么是的
{\fscx70\fscy70}Not unless you never seen a man
wash his dirty carcass before.{\r}

398
00:37:27,193 --> 00:37:30,594
小伙子，你个子不大，嘴巴倒挺能说
{\fscx70\fscy70}Boy, you got a big old pecker
for being such a little squirrel.{\r}

399
00:37:30,763 --> 00:37:32,754
你来这里看什么，迪克？
{\fscx70\fscy70}That what you come here to see, Dick?{\r}

400
00:37:34,667 --> 00:37:36,134
没什么
{\fscx70\fscy70}No.{\r}

401
00:37:37,103 --> 00:37:40,504
你哥哥说杰西在堪萨斯城多留了你几天
{\fscx70\fscy70}Your brother said that Jesse
kept you in Kansas City some extra days.{\r}

402
00:37:40,673 --> 00:37:41,731
为什么？
{\fscx70\fscy70}What was the reason?{\r}

403
00:37:43,943 --> 00:37:47,845
这个，我恐怕不方便细说
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, I'm not at liberty to say exactly.{\r}

404
00:37:48,248 --> 00:37:53,777
那我这么问你吧
杰西有提到我和康明斯在一起谋事吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Let me ask you this. Did Jesse mention
that me and Cummins were in cahoots?{\r}

405
00:37:54,954 --> 00:37:56,114
有这回事？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Is that so?{\r}

406
00:37:56,289 --> 00:38:00,225
哦，亲爱的，我说漏嘴了，是吧？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, dear. I went on and said too much,
have I?{\r}

407
00:38:00,593 --> 00:38:02,652
那么，还有谁跟你们一伙的？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, who else is partners with you two?{\r}

408
00:38:05,031 --> 00:38:09,525
听着，要是被他知道，他会割断我们的喉咙
你不像我这么了解他
{\fscx70\fscy70}See, he'll cut our throats if he finds out.
You don't know him like I do.{\r}

409
00:38:09,702 --> 00:38:13,695
谁要是跟着杰西干那些见不得人的事
然后又背着他密谋别的勾当…
{\fscx70\fscy70}You do Jesse dirt,
you connive behind his back...{\r}

410
00:38:13,873 --> 00:38:16,671
…孩子，会被他带着镰刀追杀的
{\fscx70\fscy70}...boy, he'll come after you
with a cleaver.{\r}

411
00:38:19,379 --> 00:38:21,870
那你们俩在密谋什么呢？
{\fscx70\fscy70}So, what are you two cahoots
cooking up?{\r}

412
00:38:24,884 --> 00:38:26,511
不知道我该说不该说
{\fscx70\fscy70}Don't know that I should say.{\r}

413
00:38:27,687 --> 00:38:29,780
我可不会花言巧语
骗你说出你那肮脏的小秘密
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm not gonna wheedle
the dang news from you.{\r}

414
00:38:29,956 --> 00:38:31,719
不如我们让它成为一个谜…
{\fscx70\fscy70}How about we'll leave it a mystery...{\r}

415
00:38:31,991 --> 00:38:36,189
…这样我们都不会为这次谈话后悔？
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and then we won't neither one of us
regret our little chat?{\r}

416
00:38:41,901 --> 00:38:44,665
能把那把转轮枪给我看看吗，鲍勃？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Can you hand me that six-gun there, Bob?{\r}

417
00:38:53,746 --> 00:38:57,876
如果你胆敢跟杰西提起我的事…
{\fscx70\fscy70}If you so much as mention my name
to Jesse...{\r}

418
00:38:58,051 --> 00:39:00,383
…孩子，我会知道的
{\fscx70\fscy70}...boy, I'll find out about it.{\r}

419
00:39:00,553 --> 00:39:03,545
你最好相信我
{\fscx70\fscy70}You had better believe that.{\r}

420
00:39:03,723 --> 00:39:05,748
然后我会找到你
{\fscx70\fscy70}And I'll look you up.{\r}

421
00:39:05,925 --> 00:39:10,828
敲开你的门，暴跳如雷
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'll knock on your door,
and I will be as mad as a hornet.{\r}

422
00:39:11,564 --> 00:39:13,725
我会毫不留情
{\fscx70\fscy70}I will be hot.{\r}

423
00:39:15,635 --> 00:39:18,399
注意点手上的家伙，迪克
{\fscx70\fscy70}You be careful with that iron, Dick.{\r}

424
00:39:26,713 --> 00:39:30,308
你知道我在这些问题上的立场
事情就这么简单
{\fscx70\fscy70}You know where I stand on these matters
and that's all there is to it.{\r}

425
00:39:30,483 --> 00:39:34,078
我们从此以后还是亲密无间
{\fscx70\fscy70}Me and you can be as friendly as pigs
from now on.{\r}

426
00:39:59,579 --> 00:40:03,037
我是兔崽子・福特，把手举起来！
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm Bunny Ford, stick your hands
up in the air!{\r}

427
00:40:03,216 --> 00:40:04,911
先生
{\fscx70\fscy70}Mister.{\r}

428
00:40:10,189 --> 00:40:12,419
噢，你们胆子还不小啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, you have some nerve.{\r}

429
00:40:13,726 --> 00:40:19,130
我们刚在看
詹姆斯小伙子们和墨西哥人的故事
{\fscx70\fscy70}We were just reading about the James boys
among the Mexicans.{\r}

430
00:40:20,867 --> 00:40:23,529
这是谁？这不是杰西
{\fscx70\fscy70}What's this? This ain't Jesse.{\r}

431
00:40:23,703 --> 00:40:26,831
- 你怎么知道
- 他不可能没有胡子
{\fscx70\fscy70}- You don't know that.
- He would've never wore no mustache.{\r}

432
00:40:27,006 --> 00:40:29,372
他也不可能摸过大炮
{\fscx70\fscy70}Never was anywheres near a cannon.{\r}

433
00:40:29,542 --> 00:40:31,976
让我看看这张
{\fscx70\fscy70}Let me see that picture.{\r}

434
00:40:32,145 --> 00:40:34,875
孩子，我真不知道我在看什么
{\fscx70\fscy70}Boy, I can't even calculate
what I'm looking at.{\r}

435
00:40:35,114 --> 00:40:37,241
- 给我
- 他从小时候起…
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Give me that.
- Ever since he was a child...{\r}

436
00:40:37,417 --> 00:40:40,614
…就开始收集
任何和詹姆斯兄弟有关的东西
{\fscx70\fscy70}...Bob's collected whatsoever he could find
about the James brothers.{\r}

437
00:40:40,787 --> 00:40:42,982
是啊，在房间里都搞了一个小博物馆
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah, got himself a little museum
in his room.{\r}

438
00:40:43,156 --> 00:40:46,751
下次你再来偷看，最好随身带把枪防身！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Next time you come snooping around,
you better strap on a shooting iron!{\r}

439
00:40:47,293 --> 00:40:49,784
喔，看我多害怕
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, you can see how scared I am.{\r}

440
00:40:49,962 --> 00:40:53,830
你也是，伍德・海特
再惹我，就一枪崩了你！
{\fscx70\fscy70}You too, Wood Hite. Cross me again,
I'll put a bullet through your head!{\r}

441
00:40:54,834 --> 00:40:56,028
孩子，你…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Boy, you...{\r}

442
00:40:56,703 --> 00:40:59,365
小子，你最好想想我表哥是谁…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Son, you better recollect
who my cousin is...{\r}

443
00:40:59,539 --> 00:41:03,600
…你也许忘了
杰西就像珍惜圣经一样疼我
{\fscx70\fscy70}...because you've seemed to misremembered
that Jesse loves me like the Good Book.{\r}

444
00:41:03,776 --> 00:41:07,405
现在，你可以装成一个
杂货店里的危险人物…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Now, you may play it like you're
a dangerous person in the grocery store...{\r}

445
00:41:07,580 --> 00:41:09,980
…但别忘了，如果你伤害了我的感情…
{\fscx70\fscy70}...but don't misremember
who you be accounting to...{\r}

446
00:41:10,149 --> 00:41:12,583
…你将面对的是谁
- 我才不管！
{\fscx70\fscy70}...if I so much get my feelings hurt.
- I don't care!{\r}

447
00:41:12,752 --> 00:41:14,310
是不是要我喊，“嘿哟”
{\fscx70\fscy70}Do I have to yell "suwee"?{\r}

448
00:41:14,487 --> 00:41:16,455
我们为何不先和好一阵子呢？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Why don't we make up,
be pleasant for once?{\r}

449
00:41:16,622 --> 00:41:19,455
快快乐乐的度过这个晚上，不好么？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Why don't we pass the evening
like pleasant human beings?{\r}

450
00:41:19,625 --> 00:41:21,889
衣服不错，牛仔
{\fscx70\fscy70}I like your nickel suit, cowboy.{\r}

451
00:41:47,720 --> 00:41:49,483
看到什么了吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You see something?{\r}

452
00:41:50,723 --> 00:41:52,520
一只鸟而已
{\fscx70\fscy70}Just a bird.{\r}

453
00:41:56,295 --> 00:41:58,195
十月到来了…
{\fscx70\fscy70}The month of October came...{\r}

454
00:41:58,364 --> 00:42:01,800
…杰西开始发现
私家侦探装扮成售货员…
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and Jesse began seeing
Pinkerton operatives in every floor walker...{\r}

455
00:42:01,968 --> 00:42:06,371
…扫路工和普通人在一家店里打探消息
{\fscx70\fscy70}...street sweeper, and common man
poking about in a store.{\r}

456
00:42:08,641 --> 00:42:11,166
11号的早晨，他叫醒妻子…
{\fscx70\fscy70}On the morning of the 11 th,
he would wake his wife...{\r}

457
00:42:11,344 --> 00:42:15,542
…就像圣经里，圣家逃往埃及一样
{\fscx70\fscy70}...with the Scripture pertaining to
the Holy Family's flight into Egypt.{\r}

458
00:42:19,285 --> 00:42:24,188
一夜间，托马斯・霍华德一家
就从堪萨斯市消失了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Overnight, the Thomas Howard clan
vanished from Kansas City.{\r}

459
00:42:34,667 --> 00:42:37,329
之后不久，蓝切地劫车案中的四个人…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Shortly thereafter,
four of the Blue Cut train robbers...{\r}

460
00:42:37,503 --> 00:42:40,336
…在格兰代尔附近的一间木屋里被捕
{\fscx70\fscy70}...were arrested in shacks near Glendale.{\r}

461
00:42:45,378 --> 00:42:49,075
杰西是如何预先知道的，至今还是个迷
{\fscx70\fscy70}How Jesse could have known
remains a mystery.{\r}

462
00:43:01,127 --> 00:43:04,119
他们居无定所
{\fscx70\fscy70}Theirs was a wandering existence.{\r}

463
00:43:04,297 --> 00:43:05,992
选择了犯罪这条路…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Men who choose to be outlaws...{\r}

464
00:43:06,165 --> 00:43:10,101
…就不能在一个地方呆上太久
{\fscx70\fscy70}...cannot afford to remain in one place
for very long.{\r}

465
00:43:19,145 --> 00:43:23,411
- 喔，天哪，也许我要改变主意了
- 快走，快走
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Well, goodness. Maybe I'll change my mind.
- Let's go. Let's go. Let's go.{\r}

466
00:43:23,583 --> 00:43:25,813
- 玛莎
- 忘了吧，哥们
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Martha.
- Buck up, man.{\r}

467
00:43:25,985 --> 00:43:29,546
伍德和迪克
在跨越整个肯塔基州的途中都在斗嘴
{\fscx70\fscy70}Wood and Dick would bicker
across the entire state of Kentucky...{\r}

468
00:43:29,722 --> 00:43:34,682
…一直到了罗斯威尔
伍德的父亲，也就是詹姆斯兄弟的叔叔…
{\fscx70\fscy70}...until they made Russellville, home
of Major George Hite, Wood's father...{\r}

469
00:43:34,861 --> 00:43:37,989
…乔治・海特上校的家
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and uncle to Frank and Jesse James.{\r}

470
00:43:46,072 --> 00:43:48,233
你离她远点
{\fscx70\fscy70}You stay away from this one.{\r}

471
00:43:49,008 --> 00:43:51,033
他是我爸的妻子
{\fscx70\fscy70}She's my daddy's wife.{\r}

472
00:43:51,978 --> 00:43:53,309
明白了吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You got it?{\r}

473
00:44:17,236 --> 00:44:18,863
这菜是您做的吗，太太？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Did you cook this, ma'am?{\r}

474
00:44:22,174 --> 00:44:24,438
我有个黑人女仆
{\fscx70\fscy70}I've got a nigger woman.{\r}

475
00:44:26,546 --> 00:44:27,570
他说什么？
{\fscx70\fscy70}How's that?{\r}

476
00:44:32,018 --> 00:44:35,385
迪克问菜是不是我做的
{\fscx70\fscy70}Dick asked if I cooked this.{\r}

477
00:44:35,621 --> 00:44:37,111
是你做的吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Did you?{\r}

478
00:44:39,692 --> 00:44:40,716
不是
{\fscx70\fscy70}No.{\r}

479
00:44:49,936 --> 00:44:52,370
她嫁给他的时候知道他是这样的
{\fscx70\fscy70}She knew what he was like
when she married him.{\r}

480
00:45:18,898 --> 00:45:23,130
看来我们都是夜猫子，你和我
{\fscx70\fscy70}I guess we're the night owls, you and I.{\r}

481
00:45:24,537 --> 00:45:26,368
我很高兴
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm glad.{\r}

482
00:45:28,674 --> 00:45:30,107
怎么说？
{\fscx70\fscy70}How come?{\r}

483
00:45:31,110 --> 00:45:33,704
你看起来挺有意思
{\fscx70\fscy70}You're interesting to look at.{\r}

484
00:45:34,614 --> 00:45:38,106
你的性格让人感到很舒服
{\fscx70\fscy70}You have a real pleasant disposition.{\r}

485
00:45:39,752 --> 00:45:43,688
我也说不清楚，似乎你让我感到全身温暖
{\fscx70\fscy70}And I don't know, you sort of
make me feel warm all over.{\r}

486
00:45:45,691 --> 00:45:50,355
知道吗，别人都叫我…多情浪子
{\fscx70\fscy70}You know, I'm what they call a...
An inamorato.{\r}

487
00:45:54,233 --> 00:45:58,932
嗯，我就知道你该有个外号
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, I knew
there had to be a name for it.{\r}

488
00:46:02,775 --> 00:46:04,936
如果伍德所说的片面之辞不假…
{\fscx70\fscy70}You and the Hites
don't get along too well...{\r}

489
00:46:05,111 --> 00:46:08,376
…你和海特一家相处的不大好啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}...if I'm to trust Wood and his version
of the situation.{\r}

490
00:46:09,548 --> 00:46:13,075
事实是，我们都恨透了对方
{\fscx70\fscy70}We hate each other like poison,
if you wanna know the truth.{\r}

491
00:46:13,753 --> 00:46:17,450
如果我身上着火了
海特家族大部分人都会袖手旁观
{\fscx70\fscy70}Most of the Hites wouldn't spit on me
if I was on fire.{\r}

492
00:46:19,692 --> 00:46:22,490
人们说，如果一个女人身上着了火…
{\fscx70\fscy70}They say that when a woman's on fire...{\r}

493
00:46:22,662 --> 00:46:27,099
…你应该抱着她在地上打滚
并用身体罩住她
{\fscx70\fscy70}...you're supposed to roll her around on
