- 那我想…
- 嘿
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Well, I guess that makes...
- Hey.{\r}

1006
01:43:48,471 --> 01:43:52,931
他已经干掉艾德・米勒了
还说得轻描淡写的
{\fscx70\fscy70}He already put away Ed Miller. He said so
like it was something piddly he'd done.{\r}

1007
01:44:33,916 --> 01:44:38,148
如果我们俩能单独待多过一分钟
我很想再跟你谈谈
{\fscx70\fscy70}If we're ever alone for more than a minute,
I'd like a chance to talk to you further.{\r}

1008
01:45:17,894 --> 01:45:20,124
他们给我十天时间
{\fscx70\fscy70}They gave me ten days.{\r}

1009
01:45:24,000 --> 01:45:25,524
干吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}For what?{\r}

1010
01:45:27,503 --> 01:45:29,368
逮捕他
{\fscx70\fscy70}For arresting him.{\r}

1011
01:45:35,445 --> 01:45:37,106
你和我?
{\fscx70\fscy70}You and me, huh?{\r}

1012
01:45:40,750 --> 01:45:44,015
不是他动手就是我们动手
这事躲不过的
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's gonna happen one way or another,
Charley. It's gonna happen.{\r}

1013
01:45:44,187 --> 01:45:46,781
干嘛不趁这个机会捞点钱
{\fscx70\fscy70}So it might as well be us
who get rich on it.{\r}

1014
01:45:46,956 --> 01:45:50,255
- 鲍勃，他是我们的朋友
- 他杀了艾德・米勒
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Bob, he's our friend.
- He murdered Ed Miller.{\r}

1015
01:45:50,893 --> 01:45:53,987
一有机会，他就会去杀利都和康明斯
{\fscx70\fscy70}And he's gonna murder Liddil and Cummins
if the chance ever comes.{\r}

1016
01:45:55,431 --> 01:46:00,061
照我看来，杰西正一个个地
把帮里的兄弟做掉
{\fscx70\fscy70}It seems to me Jesse's riding from
man to man, saying goodbye to the gang.{\r}

1017
01:46:01,571 --> 01:46:03,937
你的友情会害死你的
{\fscx70\fscy70}So your friendship could put you
under the pansies.{\r}

1018
01:46:06,008 --> 01:46:10,468
我会认真考虑的，鲍勃
我现在只能到这一步了
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'll grind it fine in my mind, Bob. I can't
go any further than that right now.{\r}

1019
01:46:14,050 --> 01:46:15,483
你会想通的
{\fscx70\fscy70}You'll come around.{\r}

1020
01:46:16,619 --> 01:46:19,087
你认为这都是编造的，是吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You think it's all made up, don't you?{\r}

1021
01:46:19,255 --> 01:46:22,588
他的故事只是报纸编的
{\fscx70\fscy70}You think it's all yarns
and newspaper stories.{\r}

1022
01:46:30,466 --> 01:46:32,798
他也不过是个人
{\fscx70\fscy70}He's just a human being.{\r}

1023
01:46:41,043 --> 01:46:44,171
从今以后，你们俩不许离开我行动
{\fscx70\fscy70}From now on, you two
won't go anywhere without me.{\r}

1024
01:46:44,947 --> 01:46:49,509
从今以后，你们的行动要得到我批准！
要向我请示！
{\fscx70\fscy70}From now on, you'll ask for my permission!
From now on, you'll ask to be excused!{\r}

1025
01:47:45,441 --> 01:47:49,741
查理，把马带到马棚里
鲍勃，进屋去吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley, take them horses
around the barn. Bob, you go on inside.{\r}

1026
01:47:50,580 --> 01:47:51,911
- 你好，玛丽
- 嗨
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Hello, Mary.
- Hi.{\r}

1027
01:47:52,081 --> 01:47:55,244
看我在堆肥里找到的萝卜(欧洲萝卜）
{\fscx70\fscy70}Look at this rotten parsnip
I found in the compost heap.{\r}

1028
01:48:05,461 --> 01:48:07,361
你没提过鲍勃会来
{\fscx70\fscy70}You never mentioned Bob would be here.{\r}

1029
01:48:11,634 --> 01:48:14,626
可能他想留作惊喜呢
{\fscx70\fscy70}Maybe he was saving it
as a pleasant surprise.{\r}

1030
01:48:19,242 --> 01:48:21,904
现在来了两位堂兄弟做伴了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Got two cousins for company now.{\r}

1031
01:48:31,621 --> 01:48:33,919
这么着…
{\fscx70\fscy70}How it's gonna be is...{\r}

1032
01:48:34,290 --> 01:48:38,488
我们下周一下午离开，到普拉特市
{\fscx70\fscy70}...we'll leave next Monday afternoon
and ride down to Platte City.{\r}

1033
01:48:41,364 --> 01:48:43,298
离堪萨斯市多远？
{\fscx70\fscy70}How far is that from Kansas City?{\r}

1034
01:48:45,001 --> 01:48:47,834
往南三十英里
{\fscx70\fscy70}Platte City's 30 miles south.{\r}

1035
01:48:49,472 --> 01:48:54,068
你，我和查理晚上在森林里睡一夜
{\fscx70\fscy70}You and me and Charley'll
sleep in the woods overnight...{\r}

1036
01:48:54,577 --> 01:48:58,980
我们会在关门之前一段时间
进攻富国银行
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and we'll strike the Wells Bank
sometime before the court recesses.{\r}

1037
01:49:03,786 --> 01:49:06,721
具体是几点？
{\fscx70\fscy70}What time will that be exactly?{\r}

1038
01:49:12,361 --> 01:49:14,886
这你没必要知道
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, you don't need to know that.{\r}

1039
01:49:29,912 --> 01:49:32,881
我和你哥哥一起的时候很惬意
{\fscx70\fscy70}You know, I'm real comfortable
with your brother.{\r}

1040
01:49:33,115 --> 01:49:35,640
虽然他长得难看，身上也臭
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hell, he's ugly as sin,
he smells like a skunk...{\r}

1041
01:49:36,452 --> 01:49:39,888
还无知得要命
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and he's so ignorant
he couldn't drive nails in the snow...{\r}

1042
01:49:40,056 --> 01:49:42,547
但他很好相处
{\fscx70\fscy70}...but he's sort of easy to be around.{\r}

1043
01:49:43,059 --> 01:49:45,857
你就不一样了，鲍勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}I can't say the same for you, Bob.{\r}

1044
01:49:49,265 --> 01:49:51,631
你这么说让我很难过
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, I'm sorry to hear you say that.{\r}

1045
01:49:53,502 --> 01:49:57,529
你知道那种情况吧
你和你爱人在月色之下
{\fscx70\fscy70}You know how it is when you're
with your girlfriend and the moon's out...{\r}

1046
01:49:57,707 --> 01:50:01,768
虽然她从没开口说
但你知道她等着你亲她
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and you know she wants to be kissed,
even though she never said so?{\r}

1047
01:50:05,181 --> 01:50:06,614
恩
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah.{\r}

1048
01:50:09,352 --> 01:50:12,719
你的种种迹象，让我很难过
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, you're giving me signs
that grieve my soul...{\r}

1049
01:50:13,589 --> 01:50:15,716
让我觉得…
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and make me wonder...{\r}

1050
01:50:16,125 --> 01:50:18,491
可能你对我的看法已经变了
{\fscx70\fscy70}...maybe your mind's
been changed about me.{\r}

1051
01:50:18,828 --> 01:50:22,286
你要我怎么办？向天发誓？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, what do you want me to do?
Swear my good faith on the Bible?{\r}

1052
01:50:39,782 --> 01:50:41,716
你俩在吵架？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You two having a spat?{\r}

1053
01:50:46,989 --> 01:50:49,480
我正准备发火呢
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was getting ready to be angry.{\r}

1054
01:50:54,964 --> 01:50:57,296
坐过来点，孩子
{\fscx70\fscy70}Sit over here closer, kid.{\r}

1055
01:50:59,535 --> 01:51:00,797
过来过来
{\fscx70\fscy70}Come on.{\r}

1056
01:51:11,947 --> 01:51:14,279
查理，到时你看着马
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley, you'll stay with the animals.{\r}

1057
01:51:14,950 --> 01:51:16,850
我和这孩子
{\fscx70\fscy70}Me and the kid...{\r}

1058
01:51:17,019 --> 01:51:20,978
会在中午之前走进那银行
{\fscx70\fscy70}...will walk into that bank
just before noon.{\r}

1059
01:51:22,858 --> 01:51:25,486
鲍勃会让那出纳员
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob will move that cashier...{\r}

1060
01:51:26,028 --> 01:51:29,259
没法拿到柜台底下藏着的枪
{\fscx70\fscy70}...away from the shotgun
that's under the counter...{\r}

1061
01:51:29,432 --> 01:51:32,299
然后我就溜到那出纳员后头
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and I'll creep up behind that cashier...{\r}

1062
01:51:32,468 --> 01:51:34,800
这样把他的头朝后扳
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and I'll cock his head back like so.{\r}

1063
01:51:35,071 --> 01:51:36,095
我会说
{\fscx70\fscy70}And I'll say:{\r}

1064
01:51:36,272 --> 01:51:39,002
“象你这样的废柴怎么还活着
{\fscx70\fscy70}"How come an off-scouring
like you is still sucking air...{\r}

1065
01:51:39,175 --> 01:51:41,439
而我那么多手下就已经送命了呢？”
{\fscx70\fscy70}...when so many of mine
are in coffins?" I'll say:{\r}

1066
01:51:41,610 --> 01:51:44,943
“你怎么还能活到20岁？”
{\fscx70\fscy70}"How did you get to reach 20
without leaking out all over your clothes?"{\r}

1067
01:51:45,414 --> 01:51:49,282
如果我不喜欢他的态度
我会狠狠地割掉那小子的喉咙
{\fscx70\fscy70}And if I don't like his attitude,
I will slit that phildoodle so deep...{\r}

1068
01:51:49,585 --> 01:51:52,611
让他像条脱水的鱼一样乱跳
{\fscx70\fscy70}...he will flop on the floor like a fish.{\r}

1069
01:51:56,292 --> 01:51:58,658
天啊，发生什么了？
{\fscx70\fscy70}My God, what just happened?{\r}

1070
01:52:07,903 --> 01:52:11,270
鲍勃，我能听到你的小脑袋发动了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Boy, I could hear your gears grinding...{\r}

1071
01:52:11,574 --> 01:52:14,941
听到你在问自己
“天啊，下次他会干出什么事？”
{\fscx70\fscy70}...hear your little motor wondering,
"My gosh, what's next?{\r}

1072
01:52:15,111 --> 01:52:16,476
“我会怎么样？”
{\fscx70\fscy70}What's happening to me?"{\r}

1073
01:52:18,347 --> 01:52:20,212
看你这样子，鲍勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}You were precious to behold, Bob.{\r}

1074
01:52:20,382 --> 01:52:23,010
脸白得跟墙一样
{\fscx70\fscy70}You were white as spit in a cotton field.{\r}

1075
01:52:23,552 --> 01:52:26,020
你吓到他了
{\fscx70\fscy70}You got him. You got him.{\r}

1076
01:52:27,656 --> 01:52:31,717
你想知道这是什么感觉吗？不舒服
我真的不推荐你这么做
{\fscx70\fscy70}You wanna know how that feels?
Unpleasant. I honestly can't recommend it.{\r}

1077
01:52:37,233 --> 01:52:39,701
查理看来也被吓倒了
{\fscx70\fscy70}The old Charley looked stricken!{\r}

1078
01:52:40,369 --> 01:52:42,200
是啊，是啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was. I was.{\r}

1079
01:52:42,371 --> 01:52:47,365
“太恐怖了”，查理想道
“把我一天的心情都毁了”
{\fscx70\fscy70}"This is plumb unexpected," old Charley
was thinking. "That done ruined my day."{\r}

1080
01:52:55,151 --> 01:52:56,584
天呀
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hell. Hell.{\r}

1081
01:53:27,550 --> 01:53:31,418
那晚，杰西和鲍勃睡在孩子们的房间
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse slept with Bob
in the children's room that night.{\r}

1082
01:53:32,721 --> 01:53:35,315
鲍勃一直醒着
{\fscx70\fscy70}And Bob remained awake.{\r}

1083
01:53:38,160 --> 01:53:41,527
他能看到床头柜上有一把枪
{\fscx70\fscy70}He could see that there was a gun
on the nightstand.{\r}

1084
01:53:42,398 --> 01:53:46,391
他能想象自己手里握着冰冷的枪
{\fscx70\fscy70}He could imagine its cold nickel
inside his grip...{\r}

1085
01:53:47,303 --> 01:53:50,795
举起这两磅的重量，瞄准
{\fscx70\fscy70}...its two-pound weight
reached out and aimed.{\r}

1086
01:54:21,937 --> 01:54:24,030
我要上厕所
{\fscx70\fscy70}I need to go to the privy.{\r}

1087
01:54:25,241 --> 01:54:28,642
你以为你要上，但其实你不用上
{\fscx70\fscy70}You think you do, but you don't.{\r}

1088
01:54:51,867 --> 01:54:54,028
等祷告之后再吃
{\fscx70\fscy70}You wait for grace, now.{\r}

1089
01:54:54,970 --> 01:54:58,303
- 谢谢，妈妈
- 谢谢，芝，看来很好吃哦
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Thank you, Mama.
- Thank you, Zee. God, that looks good.{\r}

1090
01:54:58,474 --> 01:55:00,101
- 谢谢，芝
- 不客气
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Thank you, Zee.
- You're welcome.{\r}

1091
01:55:00,276 --> 01:55:03,370
这适合吃还是凑合？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, is this fit to eat or will it just do?{\r}

1092
01:55:06,282 --> 01:55:08,375
她做饭可是臭名远播
{\fscx70\fscy70}Woman's cooking's
always been a scandal.{\r}

1093
01:55:08,550 --> 01:55:10,916
她做的肉，切起来整张桌子都得晃
{\fscx70\fscy70}Cut her meat and the whole table moves.{\r}

1094
01:55:11,854 --> 01:55:13,913
想吃饼干吗？想要吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You want a biscuit?
You gonna have a biscuit?{\r}

1095
01:55:14,089 --> 01:55:17,889
给你黄油，来
{\fscx70\fscy70}Here's some butter.
Come on. Come on.{\r}

1096
01:55:19,828 --> 01:55:21,125
哦，妈的
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, shoot.{\r}

1097
01:55:21,297 --> 01:55:25,097
杰西变得越来越平易近人
{\fscx70\fscy70}And so it went,
Jesse was increasingly cavalier...{\r}

1098
01:55:25,267 --> 01:55:28,998
和蔼，情绪化，沉郁
{\fscx70\fscy70}...merry, moody, fey...{\r}

1099
01:55:29,171 --> 01:55:31,264
不可预测
{\fscx70\fscy70}...unpredictable.{\r}

1100
01:55:32,808 --> 01:55:35,936
他把抑郁和狂乱隐藏起来
{\fscx70\fscy70}He camouflaged his depressions
and derangements...{\r}

1101
01:55:36,111 --> 01:55:40,104
用高度的诚恳和风度来掩饰
{\fscx70\fscy70}...with masquerades
of extreme cordiality, courtesy...{\r}

1102
01:55:40,282 --> 01:55:43,046
假装对人好心好意
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and goodwill towards others.{\r}

1103
01:55:44,119 --> 01:55:48,385
但即使他开玩笑的时候
或者给他儿子呵痒的时候
{\fscx70\fscy70}But even as he jested,
or tickled his boy in the ribs...{\r}

1104
01:55:48,557 --> 01:55:52,186
杰西都会用忧郁的眼神看着鲍勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}...Jesse would look over at Bob
with melancholy eyes...{\r}

1105
01:55:52,361 --> 01:55:56,320
两人仿佛在进行亲密深邃的交流
{\fscx70\fscy70}...as if the two were meshed
in an intimate communication.{\r}

1106
01:55:59,134 --> 01:56:01,762
鲍勃坚信杰西看穿了他
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob was certain that the man
had unriddled him...{\r}

1107
01:56:01,937 --> 01:56:04,599
看穿了他为什么跟来
{\fscx70\fscy70}...had seen through his reasons
for coming along...{\r}

1108
01:56:04,773 --> 01:56:08,766
坚信杰西能预测鲍勃任何的行动和企图
{\fscx70\fscy70}...that Jesse could forecast each of
Bob's possible moves and inclinations...{\r}

1109
01:56:08,944 --> 01:56:10,775
杰西只是在扮无辜
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and was only acting the innocent...{\r}

1110
01:56:10,946 --> 01:56:15,883
好让鲍勃放松警惕
{\fscx70\fscy70}...in order to lull Bob
into stupid tranquility and miscalculation.{\r}

1111
01:56:37,573 --> 01:56:39,768
你盯着我看多久了？
{\fscx70\fscy70}How long you been studying me?{\r}

1112
01:56:41,677 --> 01:56:44,407
你会让很多人伤心的
{\fscx70\fscy70}You're gonna break a lot of hearts.{\r}

1113
01:56:52,321 --> 01:56:53,515
什么意思？
{\fscx70\fscy70}How do you mean?{\r}

1114
01:57:02,765 --> 01:57:04,494
是份礼物
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's a present.{\r}

1115
01:57:09,171 --> 01:57:10,729
很沉
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's heavy.{\r}

1116
01:57:11,306 --> 01:57:13,433
打开看看？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, you gonna look inside?{\r}

1117
01:57:15,010 --> 01:57:16,807
今天是愚人节
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's April Fools' Day, you know.{\r}

1118
01:57:17,379 --> 01:57:19,210
这可不是个玩笑
{\fscx70\fscy70}It ain't no joke.{\r}

1119
01:57:26,722 --> 01:57:28,280
太华丽了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, such extravagance.{\r}

1120
01:57:29,825 --> 01:57:32,521
闪亮亮的，是吧？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Don't that nickel just shine, though?{\r}

1121
01:57:32,728 --> 01:57:34,286
我做梦都没想过
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's more than I could hope for.{\r}

1122
01:57:34,463 --> 01:57:37,261
你那老破枪，说不定下次开枪的时候
{\fscx70\fscy70}I figured that granddaddy Colt
may blow into fragments...{\r}

1123
01:57:37,433 --> 01:57:40,197
就得崩成一块一块的了
{\fscx70\fscy70}...next time you try
to squeeze the trigger.{\r}

1124
01:57:40,436 --> 01:57:42,836
你也许说的对
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, you might have something there.{\r}

1125
01:57:43,338 --> 01:57:45,966
汤姆，饭好了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Tom, supper's ready.{\r}

1126
01:57:47,142 --> 01:57:49,167
马上来，亲爱的
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'll be right there, sweetheart.{\r}

1127
01:57:49,344 --> 01:57:51,642
我太兴奋了，都吃不下饭了
{\fscx70\fscy70}I might be too excited to eat.{\r}

1128
01:57:54,917 --> 01:57:57,408
你知道约翰・纽曼・爱德华兹
曾经怎么写我吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You know what John Newman Edwards
once wrote about me?{\r}

1129
01:57:58,454 --> 01:58:01,287
他说，给我一万个人
我只能找出两个能信任的人
{\fscx70\fscy70}He said I didn't trust
two men in 10,000...{\r}

1130
01:58:01,457 --> 01:58:04,119
就算和这俩人一起，我还是很警惕
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and even them I was cautious around.{\r}

1131
01:58:04,927 --> 01:58:06,918
政府长年追捕，让我疲惫不堪
{\fscx70\fscy70}Government's sort of run me ragged.{\r}

1132
01:58:08,897 --> 01:58:11,889
我绕着圈子说话呢
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm going the long way around the barn
to say that...{\r}

1133
01:58:12,067 --> 01:58:15,696
我是被追急了，最近有时故意刁难人
{\fscx70\fscy70}...I been feeling cornered
and just plain ornery as of late...{\r}

1134
01:58:16,438 --> 01:58:21,102
如果你能接受这把枪，接受我的歉意
我会很高兴的
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and I'd be pleased if you'd accept
that gun as my way of apologizing.{\r}

1135
01:58:23,479 --> 01:58:26,277
如果我是你，我大概会更加刁难人
{\fscx70\fscy70}Heaven knows I'd be ornerier
if I were in your position.{\r}

1136
01:58:26,448 --> 01:58:29,542
不，不，我的行为是不对的
{\fscx70\fscy70}No. No, I haven't been acting correctly.{\r}

1137
01:58:31,353 --> 01:58:34,880
我有时候都认不出自己了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Seems I hardly recognize myself
when I'm greased.{\r}

1138
01:58:37,960 --> 01:58:40,451
我有时候灵魂出窍
{\fscx70\fscy70}I go on journeys out of my body...{\r}

1139
01:58:40,629 --> 01:58:44,725
看到自己这染血的手和凶恶的脸
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and look at my red hands
and my mean face...{\r}

1140
01:58:45,501 --> 01:58:49,232
看着这个做了那么多错事的人
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and I wonder about that man
that's gone so wrong.{\r}

1141
01:58:53,008 --> 01:58:56,034
我对自己来说，都已经成了一个麻烦
{\fscx70\fscy70}I've been becoming a problem to myself.{\r}

1142
01:59:08,690 --> 01:59:10,055
唉
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well...{\r}

1143
01:59:16,698 --> 01:59:21,328
- 该吃饭了，我去洗手
- 恩，去吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}- I better wash my hands if supper's on.
- Yeah, go ahead.{\r}

1144
01:59:34,683 --> 01:59:37,618
他死前一天是主进圣城节
{\fscx70\fscy70}The day before he died was Palm Sunday.{\r}

1145
01:59:38,654 --> 01:59:41,953
汤玛斯・霍华德先生和他的夫人，
还有他们的两个孩子
{\fscx70\fscy70}And Mr. And Mrs. Thomas Howard,
their two children...{\r}

1146
01:59:42,124 --> 01:59:44,183
还有他们的表亲查尔斯・约翰森
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and their cousin Charles Johnson...{\r}

1147
01:59:44,359 --> 01:59:49,524
到第二长老会教堂参加10点的礼拜
{\fscx70\fscy70}...strolled to the Second Presbyterian
Church to attend the 10:00 service.{\r}

1148
01:59:51,934 --> 01:59:54,232
鲍勃留在了屋里
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob remained at the cottage...{\r}

1149
01:59:54,403 --> 01:59:57,804
偷偷地从一个房间，走到另一个房间
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and slyly migrated from room to room.{\r}

1150
02:00:00,409 --> 02:00:02,240
他走进主人房
{\fscx70\fscy70}He walked into the master bedroom...{\r}

1151
02:00:02,411 --> 02:00:06,177
把里面的衣服翻了一遍
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and inventoried the clothes
on the hangers and hooks.{\r}

1152
02:00:12,487 --> 02:00:15,820
拿起化妆台上的一杯水，喝了一口
{\fscx70\fscy70}He sipped from the water glass
on the vanity.{\r}

1153
02:00:18,160 --> 02:00:22,426
闻了闻杰西枕套上的滑石粉和丁香花
{\fscx70\fscy70}He smelled the talcum and lilacs
on Jesse's pillowcase.{\r}

1154
02:00:30,339 --> 02:00:32,534
他的手指滑过自己的肋骨
{\fscx70\fscy70}His fingers skittered over his ribs...{\r}

1155
02:00:32,708 --> 02:00:36,576
想象上面像杰西那样，有两次中枪的伤疤
{\fscx70\fscy70}...to construe the scars
where Jesse was twice shot.{\r}

1156
02:00:40,382 --> 02:00:44,978
他把中指弄成上两个关节没了那样
{\fscx70\fscy70}He manufactured a middle finger
that was missing the top two knuckles.{\r}

1157
02:00:52,427 --> 02:00:55,362
想象自己34岁
{\fscx70\fscy70}He imagined himself at 34.{\r}

1158
02:00:57,366 --> 02:01:00,358
想象自己躺在了棺材里
{\fscx70\fscy70}He imagined himself in a coffin.{\r}

1159
02:01:02,437 --> 02:01:04,166
他想到各种各样
{\fscx70\fscy70}He considered possibilities...{\r}

1160
02:01:04,339 --> 02:01:07,638
即将成真的好事情
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and everything wonderful
that could come true.{\r}

1161
02:01:35,437 --> 02:01:37,371
他不会杀我们的
{\fscx70\fscy70}He's not gonna kill us.{\r}

1162
02:01:42,611 --> 02:01:44,772
他会的
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah, he is.{\r}

1163
02:01:47,082 --> 02:01:49,573
我会一直醒着，他就没法下手了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, I'll stay awake so he can't.{\r}

1164
02:02:02,931 --> 02:02:05,365
你在瞎想
{\fscx70\fscy70}You're imagining things.{\r}

1165
02:02:17,612 --> 02:02:19,580
不会去什么普拉特市
{\fscx70\fscy70}Ain't gonna be no Platte City.{\r}

1166
02:02:21,316 --> 02:02:23,944
杰西只是在耍我们
{\fscx70\fscy70}That's Jesse fooling with us.{\r}

1167
02:02:40,369 --> 02:02:42,599
睡吧，查理
{\fscx70\fscy70}Go to sleep, Charley.{\r}

1168
02:02:54,200 --> 02:02:57,200
[1882年4月3日]

1169
02:03:16,204 --> 02:03:17,796
早
{\fscx70\fscy70}Morning.{\r}

1170
02:03:21,610 --> 02:03:23,134
查理
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley.{\r}

1171
02:03:52,974 --> 02:03:55,408
鲍勃，你要吃多少？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob, how much did you want to eat?{\r}

1172
02:03:59,915 --> 02:04:02,349
我感觉有点怪怪的
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm feeling sort of peculiar.{\r}

1173
02:04:21,570 --> 02:04:24,038
为什么那么感兴趣地看着我们？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Why is it you're looking so interested?{\r}

1174
02:04:25,507 --> 02:04:28,408
你以为这样出去晃很聪明？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You think it's intelligent
to go out like that...{\r}

1175
02:04:28,577 --> 02:04:30,408
让大家都看见你的枪？
{\fscx70\fscy70}...so all creation can see your guns?{\r}

1176
02:04:48,163 --> 02:04:49,596
嗨
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hi.{\r}

1177
02:04:59,908 --> 02:05:02,809
来，看你妈妈在干吗
{\fscx70\fscy70}Come on, let's go see
what your mama's doing.{\r}

1178
02:05:03,945 --> 02:05:06,072
提米，开门
{\fscx70\fscy70}Timmy, get that door, would you?{\r}

1179
02:05:10,218 --> 02:05:13,381
- 你弄丢了一只鞋是吗，亲爱的
- 是啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Well, you lost your shoe, sweetheart.
- Yeah, I did.{\r}

1180
02:05:13,555 --> 02:05:17,685
那可麻烦了，商店也不单只卖呀
{\fscx70\fscy70}That's gonna be a problem.
They don't sell those one at a time.{\r}

1181
02:05:19,194 --> 02:05:21,253
我们丢了一只鞋，妈妈
{\fscx70\fscy70}We lost a shoe, Mama.{\r}

1182
02:05:22,864 --> 02:05:25,424
帮爸爸穿上，好吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Will you put that up for Daddy,
would you?{\r}

1183
02:05:28,503 --> 02:05:31,267
- 你在干吗，丢了一只鞋？
- 恩
{\fscx70\fscy70}- What you doing, you lose a shoe?
- Yeah.{\r}

1184
02:05:34,782 --> 02:05:38,488
[迪克・利都被逮捕，并已认罪]

1185
02:05:47,989 --> 02:05:51,390
只会往上，作为补充
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's only meant to go on top,
to complement.{\r}

1186
02:05:51,660 --> 02:05:53,491
我知道，有时候，我
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah, I know. Sometimes, l...{\r}

1187
02:06:18,086 --> 02:06:20,987
鲍勃，菜要凉了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob, everything's getting cold!{\r}

1188
02:06:21,690 --> 02:06:25,091
- 玛丽在哪里？
- 在外面，亲爱的
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Where's Mary?
- She's outside, darling.{\r}

1189
02:06:26,094 --> 02:06:27,891
玛丽？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Mary?{\r}

1190
02:06:31,666 --> 02:06:34,191
你说他那小脑瓜里都在想什么？
{\fscx70\fscy70}What do you think goes on
in that noggin of his?{\r}

1191
02:06:37,205 --> 02:06:38,900
没什么
{\fscx70\fscy70}Nothing.{\r}

1192
02:06:39,474 --> 02:06:42,272
我说的是他，不是你
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was talking about his mind, not yours.{\r}

1193
02:06:43,211 --> 02:06:44,940
哦，是啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, yeah.{\r}

1194
02:06:45,380 --> 02:06:47,075
哈，我明白
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, I get it.{\r}

1195
02:07:42,504 --> 02:07:44,472
啊哈
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, hello now.{\r}

1196
02:07:44,873 --> 02:07:47,899
“迪克・利都被逮捕，并已认罪”
{\fscx70\fscy70}"The arrest and confession
of Dick Liddil."{\r}

1197
02:07:53,148 --> 02:07:55,309
不是吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}You don't say so.{\r}

1198
02:08:09,631 --> 02:08:11,724
真怪了
{\fscx70\fscy70}That's very strange.{\r}

1199
02:08:12,167 --> 02:08:15,068
上面说迪克三星期前就投降了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Says here Dick surrendered
three weeks ago.{\r}

1200
02:08:15,236 --> 02:08:17,830
那时候你应该在那附近吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}You must have been
right in the neighborhood.{\r}

1201
02:08:18,506 --> 02:08:21,134
很明显，他们是秘密行动
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, apparently, they kept it a secret.{\r}

1202
02:08:32,353 --> 02:08:35,413
如果我短期内去堪萨斯市，会找人问问
{\fscx70\fscy70}If I get to Kansas City soon,
I'll ask somebody about it.{\r}

1203
02:09:16,097 --> 02:09:17,792
你俩准备好了吗
{\fscx70\fscy70}You two ready?{\r}

1204
02:09:21,503 --> 02:09:24,165
马上就好
{\fscx70\fscy70}I will be, by noon.{\r}

1205
02:09:57,071 --> 02:09:59,733
她要上船，航行出海
{\fscx70\fscy70}There is a ship
She sails the sea{\r}

1206
02:09:59,908 --> 02:10:02,672
她装了很多很多东西
{\fscx70\fscy70}She's loaded deep
As deep can be{\r}

1207
02:10:02,844 --> 02:10:05,074
但不及我对她的爱多
{\fscx70\fscy70}But not as deep
As the love I'm in{\r}

1208
02:10:05,647 --> 02:10:09,276
我不知道我是浮是沉
{\fscx70\fscy70}I know not if I sink or swim{\r}

1209
02:10:10,318 --> 02:10:12,013
海水广阔
{\fscx70\fscy70}The water is wide{\r}

1210
02:10:13,154 --> 02:10:19,718
我游不过，也没法翱翔而过
{\fscx70\fscy70}I can't cross o'er
And neither have I wings to fly{\r}

1211
02:10:20,161 --> 02:10:23,961
给我一只能载两个人的小船
{\fscx70\fscy70}Give me a boat
That can carry two{\r}

1212
02:10:24,132 --> 02:10:26,999
一起划船，我和我的爱人
{\fscx70\fscy70}Both shall row
My love and I{\r}

1213
02:10:27,168 --> 02:10:30,626
柔情款款
{\fscx70\fscy70}For love is gentle
And love is kind{\r}

1214
02:10:30,805 --> 02:10:33,797
如初开花蕾，芬芳扑鼻
{\fscx70\fscy70}Sweetest flower
When first it's new{\r}

1215
02:10:33,975 --> 02:10:37,570
但热情一旦冷却
{\fscx70\fscy70}But love grows old
And waxes cold{\r}

1216
02:10:37,745 --> 02:10:40,976
就像晨露一样枯萎
{\fscx70\fscy70}And fades away
Like the morning dew{\r}

1217
02:10:41,149 --> 02:10:44,175
她要上船，航行出海
{\fscx70\fscy70}There is a ship
She sails the sea{\r}

1218
02:10:44,352 --> 02:10:47,116
我该把枪拿下来
{\fscx70\fscy70}I guess I'll take my guns off...{\r}

1219
02:10:47,455 --> 02:10:49,446
别让邻居看到
{\fscx70\fscy70}...for fear the neighbors might spy them.{\r}

1220
02:11:22,757 --> 02:11:25,191
这画怎么那么多灰？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Don't that picture look dusty?{\r}

1221
02:13:07,295 --> 02:13:10,287
你…你做了什么？
{\fscx70\fscy70}What have...? What have you done?{\r}

1222
02:13:12,734 --> 02:13:14,361
杰西
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse.{\r}

1223
02:13:19,907 --> 02:13:20,931
杰西？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse?{\r}

1224
02:13:22,076 --> 02:13:24,203
杰西？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse? Jesse?{\r}

1225
02:13:24,946 --> 02:13:26,811
杰西！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse!{\r}

1226
02:13:27,815 --> 02:13:29,908
不!
{\fscx70\fscy70}No!{\r}

1227
02:13:34,088 --> 02:13:36,420
别，杰西
{\fscx70\fscy70}No. Jess...{\r}

1228
02:13:37,025 --> 02:13:41,428
回来，回来
{\fscx70\fscy70}Come back. Oh, come back.{\r}

1229
02:13:43,564 --> 02:13:47,728
杰西，不要！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, Jesse! No!{\r}

1230
02:13:48,236 --> 02:13:52,138
鲍勃，是你干的吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, Bob. Have you done this?!{\r}

1231
02:13:52,340 --> 02:13:54,706
我向上帝发誓，我没有
{\fscx70\fscy70}I swear to God I didn't.{\r}

1232
02:13:55,710 --> 02:13:57,143
是场意外，芝
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was an accident, Zee.{\r}

1233
02:13:59,347 --> 02:14:02,714
枪走火了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Come on. Pistol went off accidentally.{\r}

1234
02:14:48,062 --> 02:14:49,256
[州长：我杀了杰西・詹姆斯]
写上我的名字
{\fscx70\fscy70}Put my name.{\r}

1235
02:14:49,430 --> 02:14:51,898
[州长：我杀了杰西・詹姆斯。罗伯特・福特]
你做什么了？我杀了他
{\fscx70\fscy70}Why, what'd you do? I shot him.{\r}

1236
02:14:59,107 --> 02:15:01,132
你大概会想留着它
{\fscx70\fscy70}You might wanna keep that.{\r}

1237
02:15:39,080 --> 02:15:41,173
谢谢
{\fscx70\fscy70}Thank you all very much.{\r}

1238
02:15:49,323 --> 02:15:51,814
照片以每张２美元的价钱卖出
{\fscx70\fscy70}The resulting prints
sold for 2 dollars apiece...{\r}

1239
02:15:51,993 --> 02:15:56,589
好些杂志拿来做了封面
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and were the models for the lithographed
covers on a number of magazines.{\r}

1240
02:16:02,136 --> 02:16:07,335
成千的陌生人像着了魔一样
来到这房子来朝圣
{\fscx70\fscy70}Soon a thousand strangers were making
spellbound pilgrimages to the cottage...{\r}

1241
02:16:07,708 --> 02:16:12,236
到森丹法邓的冷藏室去瞻仰
{\fscx70\fscy70}...or were venerating the iced remains
in Seidenfaden's cooling room.{\r}

1242
02:16:13,147 --> 02:16:17,641
有个人，曾经出价３万美元，想买下
刺杀加菲尔德・詹姆士总统那杀手的尸体
{\fscx70\fscy70}The man who offered 30,000 dollars for
the body of President Garfield's assassin...{\r}

1243
02:16:17,818 --> 02:16:21,720
他给该市警长克雷格打了个电报，出价５万
{\fscx70\fscy70}...sent a telegram to City Marshal
Enos Craig offering 50,000...{\r}

1244
02:16:21,889 --> 02:16:24,187
想买下杰西・詹姆斯的遗体
{\fscx70\fscy70}...for the body
of Jesse Woodson James...{\r}

1245
02:16:24,358 --> 02:16:27,122
准备全国展览
{\fscx70\fscy70}...so that he could go around the country
with it...{\r}

1246
02:16:29,530 --> 02:16:34,490
或者至少卖给P・T・巴纳姆，在其表演里展出
（美国著名游艺节目演出的经理人）
{\fscx70\fscy70}...or at least sell it to P.T. Barnum
for his Greatest Show on Earth.{\r}

1247
02:16:38,573 --> 02:16:41,667
另外一张照片，拍的是这位美国著名大盗
{\fscx70\fscy70}Another photograph was taken
of the renowned American bandit...{\r}

1248
02:16:41,842 --> 02:16:44,436
躺在冰床上
{\fscx70\fscy70}...nestled in his bed of ice.{\r}

1249
02:16:44,612 --> 02:16:48,878
这张照片在小店和药房等地方都大卖
{\fscx70\fscy70}And it was this shot that was most
available in sundries and apothecaries...{\r}

1250
02:16:49,050 --> 02:16:52,713
大家透过立体透镜来看这照片
就像看狮身人面像
{\fscx70\fscy70}...to be viewed in a stereoscope
alongside the sphinx...{\r}

1251
02:16:52,887 --> 02:16:56,880
泰姬陵和罗马的地下墓室
这些名胜古迹的照片一样
{\fscx70\fscy70}...the Taj Mahal,
and the catacombs of Rome.{\r}

1252
02:17:22,083 --> 02:17:24,051
看啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hello, here!{\r}

1253
02:17:24,252 --> 02:17:26,846
“迪克・利都被逮捕，并已认罪”
{\fscx70\fscy70}"The arrest and confession
of Dick Liddil."{\r}

1254
02:17:27,021 --> 02:17:32,152
年轻人，你跟我说过
不知道迪克投降了是吧？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Young man, I thought you told me
you didn't know Dick had surrendered.{\r}

1255
02:17:32,326 --> 02:17:36,194
真的吗？我不知道
{\fscx70\fscy70}You mean he did? I didn't know.{\r}

1256
02:17:37,098 --> 02:17:38,998
但我知道我骗不了他
{\fscx70\fscy70}But I knew I had not fooled him.{\r}

1257
02:17:39,166 --> 02:17:43,000
他和我一样心知肚明，那一刻我准备
把他绳之于法
{\fscx70\fscy70}And he knew, as well as I, in that moment
that I intended to bring him to justice.{\r}

1258
02:17:43,938 --> 02:17:47,499
但他不会当着他老婆孩子的面杀我
{\fscx70\fscy70}But he would not kill me
in the presence of his wife and children.{\r}

1259
02:17:47,675 --> 02:17:50,906
所以他笑了，好让我放松警惕
{\fscx70\fscy70}And so he was smiling
to throw me off-guard.{\r}

1260
02:17:54,148 --> 02:17:56,810
哦，对阿，鲍勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, it's all right, anyway, Bob.{\r}

1261
02:17:58,686 --> 02:18:01,587
大家都认为，鲍勃相当具有戏剧天赋
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was widely felt that
Bob possessed some acting talent...{\r}

1262
02:18:01,756 --> 02:18:04,020
而查理则一点天分都没有
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and Charley, not a jot.{\r}

1263
02:18:04,191 --> 02:18:07,126
这画怎么那么多灰呀
{\fscx70\fscy70}That picture's awful dusty.{\r}

1264
02:18:07,928 --> 02:18:11,056
大家希望查理不要那么垂头丧气，喃喃自语
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley was only expected
not to slouch or mutter...{\r}

1265
02:18:11,232 --> 02:18:15,896
不要把这种心情传给观众
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and to transport his sicknesses
to the alley before letting them go.{\r}

1266
02:18:45,299 --> 02:18:47,164
就这样
{\fscx70\fscy70}And that's...{\r}

1267
02:18:47,735 --> 02:18:50,397
我杀了杰西・詹姆斯
{\fscx70\fscy70}...how I killed Jesse James.{\r}

1268
02:18:53,874 --> 02:18:57,401
到了1883年3月，认得鲍勃・福特的人
{\fscx70\fscy70}By October of 1883, Bob Ford
could be identified correctly...{\r}

1269
02:18:57,578 --> 02:19:01,844
已经比认得美国总统的人多了
{\fscx70\fscy70}...by more citizens than could
the president of the United States.{\r}

1270
02:19:02,516 --> 02:19:07,249
年仅20岁，他已经非常出名，可以媲美
杰西犯了14年偷窃罪所累积出来的名气
{\fscx70\fscy70}He was as renowned at 20 as Jesse was
after 14 years of grand larceny.{\r}

1271
02:19:07,421 --> 02:19:09,616
你不会勾引到我的
{\fscx70\fscy70}You won't get your hooks into me.{\r}

1272
02:19:10,157 --> 02:19:14,890
对了，这就对了，坐到你男朋友边上，吉贝尔
{\fscx70\fscy70}That's right. That's right.
Sit next to your boyfriend. Jezebel.{\r}

1273
02:19:15,062 --> 02:19:17,155
查理变得越发的迷信
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley was increasingly superstitious...{\r}

1274
02:19:17,331 --> 02:19:20,027
越发相信占卜者的建议
{\fscx70\fscy70}...increasingly subject
to the advice of soothsayers...{\r}

1275
02:19:20,201 --> 02:19:24,228
占卜者声称能用烟斗和糊药治愈他的悲伤
{\fscx70\fscy70}...who promised to cure his miseries
with pipe smoke and poultices.{\r}

1276
02:19:24,405 --> 02:19:27,670
你见吉普赛人见得太多了，查理
{\fscx70\fscy70}You been spending too much time
with Gypsies, Charley.{\r}

1277
02:19:33,381 --> 02:19:34,746
靠
{\fscx70\fscy70}Shit.{\r}

1278
02:19:39,086 --> 02:19:41,646
这照片怎么那么多灰
{\fscx70\fscy70}The picture's awful dusty.{\r}

1279
02:19:42,089 --> 02:19:45,923
查理对杰西的演绎方式发生了变化
{\fscx70\fscy70}Something began to change
in Charley's stage portrayal of Jesse.{\r}

1280
02:19:46,093 --> 02:19:48,618
他的步态显得更娴熟
{\fscx70\fscy70}His gait seemed more practiced.{\r}

1281
02:19:48,796 --> 02:19:52,095
声音越发和那人相似，让人毛骨悚然
{\fscx70\fscy70}His voice was spookily similar
to the man's.{\r}

1282
02:19:52,266 --> 02:19:54,666
他新加入了一些对话
{\fscx70\fscy70}His newly suggested dialogue
was analogous...{\r}

1283
02:19:54,835 --> 02:19:57,861
仿佛出自杰西的创造
{\fscx70\fscy70}...to a script Jesse might have originated.{\r}

1284
02:20:00,674 --> 02:20:03,108
他开始用蔑视的眼神注视他的弟弟
{\fscx70\fscy70}He began to look at his younger brother
with spite...{\r}

1285
02:20:03,277 --> 02:20:05,905
仿佛他疑心，在以后的演出里
{\fscx70\fscy70}...as if he suspected that
in some future performance...{\r}

1286
02:20:06,080 --> 02:20:10,608
他将面对罗伯特・福特的真枪实弹
{\fscx70\fscy70}...he might present himself
to a live cartridge in Robert Ford's gun.{\r}

1287
02:20:11,952 --> 02:20:13,783
杀人犯！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Murderer!{\r}

1288
02:20:14,121 --> 02:20:15,850
杂种！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Cur!{\r}

1289
02:20:16,490 --> 02:20:18,253
懦夫！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Coward!{\r}

1290
02:20:21,796 --> 02:20:26,324
你想看我有多大的胆子是吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You wanna investigate my courage?
Do you?{\r}

1291
02:20:26,734 --> 02:20:30,500
来啊！来啊！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Find out! Find out!{\r}

1292
02:20:35,142 --> 02:20:37,007
没人来
{\fscx70\fscy70}Nobody.{\r}

1293
02:20:51,592 --> 02:20:53,389
懦夫！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Coward!{\r}

1294
02:21:18,586 --> 02:21:24,149
据他自己估计
鲍勃谋杀了杰西・詹姆斯800多次
{\fscx70\fscy70}By his own approximation, Bob
assassinated Jesse James over 800 times.{\r}

1295
02:21:24,325 --> 02:21:28,091
他猜，历史上没有任何人
曾这样频繁，或如此公开地
{\fscx70\fscy70}He suspected no one in history
had ever so often or so publicly...{\r}

1296
02:21:28,262 --> 02:21:31,459
重演一次背叛的行为
{\fscx70\fscy70}...recapitulated an act of betrayal.{\r}

1297
02:21:36,670 --> 02:21:39,434
鲍勃经常挑战对于懦夫的定义
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob always challenged
the allegations of cowardice...{\r}

1298
02:21:39,607 --> 02:21:42,542
但查理似乎认同这些定义
{\fscx70\fscy70}...but Charley seemed
to agree with them.{\r}

1299
02:21:42,810 --> 02:21:46,576
他提起芝・詹姆斯太太的时候
把她说得像圣母一样
{\fscx70\fscy70}He spoke of Mrs. Zee James
as certain priests might the Madonna...{\r}

1300
02:21:46,747 --> 02:21:49,841
还给她写了许多发自肺腑的长信
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and composed long soul-describing letters
to her...{\r}

1301
02:21:50,017 --> 02:21:52,212
请求她的原谅
{\fscx70\fscy70}...begging her forgiveness...{\r}

1302
02:21:53,521 --> 02:21:56,115
但这些信从未寄出过
{\fscx70\fscy70}...none of which he mailed.{\r}

1303
02:22:23,984 --> 02:22:29,581
大家觉得，暗杀了杰西・詹姆斯的人
下场就该和查理・福特一样
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley Ford became all that his countrymen
wanted an assassin of Jesse James to be.{\r}

1304
02:22:33,861 --> 02:22:39,731
杰西・詹姆斯杀了很多人
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse James was a man
Who killed many men{\r}

1305
02:22:40,935 --> 02:22:45,372
他抢了格伦代尔火车
{\fscx70\fscy70}He robbed the Glendale train{\r}

1306
02:22:45,606 --> 02:22:51,442
他劫富济贫
{\fscx70\fscy70}And he stole from the rich
And he gave to the poor{\r}

1307
02:22:51,679 --> 02:22:56,616
他身手敏捷，头脑机灵
{\fscx70\fscy70}He had a hand
And a heart and a brain{\r}

1308
02:22:57,418 --> 02:23:02,913
杰西有个妻子，她会为他哀悼
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, Jesse had a wife
To mourn for his life{\r}

1309
02:23:03,090 --> 02:23:08,187
还有三个勇敢的儿女
{\fscx70\fscy70}Three children
They were brave{\r}

1310
02:23:08,362 --> 02:23:13,959
但那个肮脏的懦夫，射杀了霍华德先生
{\fscx70\fscy70}But that dirty little coward
Who shot Mr. Howard{\r}

1311
02:23:14,201 --> 02:23:19,264
让杰西・詹姆斯进了棺材
{\fscx70\fscy70}Has laid Jesse James in his grave{\r}

1312
02:23:20,341 --> 02:23:25,335
罗伯特・福特，这肮脏的小懦夫
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was Robert Ford
That dirty little coward{\r}

1313
02:23:26,080 --> 02:23:30,483
我想知道他的感受
{\fscx70\fscy70}I wonder how does he feel{\r}

1314
02:23:30,651 --> 02:23:36,385
他吃杰西的饭，睡杰西的床
{\fscx70\fscy70}For he ate at Jesse's bread
And he slept in Jesse's bed{\r}

1315
02:23:36,557 --> 02:23:41,585
却让可怜的杰西进了棺材
{\fscx70\fscy70}And he laid poor Jesse in his grave{\r}

1316
02:23:42,062 --> 02:23:47,591
杰西有个妻子，她会为他哀悼
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, Jesse had a wife
To mourn for his life{\r}

1317
02:23:47,768 --> 02:23:52,671
还有三个勇敢的儿女
{\fscx70\fscy70}Three children
They were brave{\r}

1318
02:23:52,840 --> 02:23:58,472
但那个肮脏的懦夫，射杀了霍华德先生
{\fscx70\fscy70}But that dirty little coward
Who shot Mr. Howard{\r}

1319
02:23:58,646 --> 02:24:02,810
让可怜的杰西进了棺材
{\fscx70\fscy70}Has laid poor Jesse in his grave{\r}

1320
02:24:14,361 --> 02:24:16,386
我就是罗伯特・福特
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm Robert Ford.{\r}

1321
02:24:27,107 --> 02:24:30,838
是两个孩子，不是三个
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was two children, not three.{\r}

1322
02:24:42,222 --> 02:24:43,553
嘿
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hey.{\r}

1323
02:24:44,458 --> 02:24:47,018
回家去，好吗
{\fscx70\fscy70}You get yourself home, son, okay?{\r}

1324
02:24:47,728 --> 02:24:51,755
出去，滚出我的地方
{\fscx70\fscy70}Come on. Get out of here.
Get out of my place.{\r}

1325
02:25:23,530 --> 02:25:25,725
他生气极了的时候
{\fscx70\fscy70}He thought, at his angriest...{\r}

1326
02:25:25,899 --> 02:25:29,665
会想去见杰西杀害的人的家属
{\fscx70\fscy70}...about visiting the kin
of Jesse's slaughtered victims:{\r}

1327
02:25:31,638 --> 02:25:34,903
普拉茨堡的威廉太太
{\fscx70\fscy70}Mrs. William Westfall in Plattsburg...{\r}

1328
02:25:37,411 --> 02:25:40,505
克莱县的崴墨一家
{\fscx70\fscy70}...the Wymore family in Clay County...{\r}

1329
02:25:45,652 --> 02:25:49,952
甚至是马萨诸塞州北田的
约瑟夫・黑伍德的遗孀
{\fscx70\fscy70}...perhaps even Mrs. Joseph Heywood
in Northfield, Minnesota.{\r}

1330
02:25:53,026 --> 02:25:56,018
他想到这些人的家里
告诉他们他叫罗伯特・詹姆斯
{\fscx70\fscy70}He would go to their homes
and give his name as Robert Ford...{\r}

1331
02:25:56,196 --> 02:25:59,165
告诉他们他杀了杰西・詹姆斯
{\fscx70\fscy70}...the man who killed Jesse James.{\r}

1332
02:26:00,601 --> 02:26:03,661
他想象他们会对他充满感激之情
{\fscx70\fscy70}He imagined they would
be grateful to him.{\r}

1333
02:26:54,621 --> 02:26:59,615
他只对多莱西・伊凡思坦白道出了真相
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was only with Dorothy Evans
that Bob spoke revealingly or plainly...{\r}

1334
02:26:59,793 --> 02:27:04,230
告诉她一些他以前都不知道自己知道的事情
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and it was with her that he spoke of
things he didn't know he knew.{\r}

1335
02:27:25,886 --> 02:27:29,947
他告诉她，他对射杀和后事都没有真实的记忆
{\fscx70\fscy70}He told her that he had no real memory
of the shooting and its aftermath.{\r}

1336
02:27:30,123 --> 02:27:33,991
他只记得，举起了那把杰西给他的枪
{\fscx70\fscy70}He could remember lifting the gun
that Jesse had given him...{\r}

1337
02:27:34,728 --> 02:27:38,755
然后就到耶稣受难日了，他看到了葬礼安排
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and then it was Good Friday and he was
reading about the funeral proceedings...{\r}

1338
02:27:38,932 --> 02:27:41,457
仿佛事情已经过去了很久
{\fscx70\fscy70}...as if they'd happened a long time ago.{\r}

1339
02:27:43,036 --> 02:27:45,163
你为什么杀了他？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Why did you kill him?{\r}

1340
02:27:49,476 --> 02:27:51,501
他要杀我
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, he was gonna kill me.{\r}

1341
02:27:56,717 --> 02:27:59,948
那唯一的原因就是你害怕了？
{\fscx70\fscy70}So you were scared
and that's the only reason?{\r}

1342
02:28:02,689 --> 02:28:04,088
对
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah.{\r}

1343
02:28:04,558 --> 02:28:06,617
还有赏金
{\fscx70\fscy70}And the reward money.{\r}

1344
02:28:12,432 --> 02:28:15,230
你想我换个话题吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Do you want me to change the subject?{\r}

1345
02:28:23,443 --> 02:28:25,775
你知道我曾经期待什么吗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You know what I expected?{\r}

1346
02:28:26,813 --> 02:28:28,804
掌声
{\fscx70\fscy70}Applause.{\r}

1347
02:28:31,385 --> 02:28:35,549
我那时候才20岁，我不知道别人会怎么看
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was only 20 years old then.
I couldn't see how it would look to people.{\r}

1348
02:28:39,660 --> 02:28:42,322
事情竟变成这样，我很吃惊
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was surprised by what happened.{\r}

1349
02:28:43,397 --> 02:28:45,365
他们没有鼓掌
{\fscx70\fscy70}They didn't applaud.{\r}

1350
02:28:48,802 --> 02:28:50,667
他为自己的吹嘘
{\fscx70\fscy70}He was ashamed of his boasting...{\r}

1351
02:28:50,837 --> 02:28:53,704
自己假装的勇敢无畏而感到羞耻
{\fscx70\fscy70}...his pretensions of courage
and ruthlessness.{\r}

1352
02:28:54,007 --> 02:28:57,773
他为自己的冷血无情
{\fscx70\fscy70}He was sorry about his cold-bloodedness,
his dispassion...{\r}

1353
02:28:59,413 --> 02:29:03,816
为自己无法表达自己真实的感情而充满愧疚
{\fscx70\fscy70}...his inability to express
what he now believed was the case:{\r}

1354
02:29:06,386 --> 02:29:09,412
他很后悔杀了杰西
{\fscx70\fscy70}That he truly regretted killing Jesse...{\r}

1355
02:29:10,190 --> 02:29:13,182
他非常想念他
{\fscx70\fscy70}...that he missed the man
as much as anybody...{\r}

1356
02:29:13,727 --> 02:29:16,855
他希望，他不是非要杀了杰西来保命
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and wished his murder
hadn't been necessary.{\r}

1357
02:29:36,316 --> 02:29:38,409
即使当他在自己的酒吧里穿行
{\fscx70\fscy70}Even as he circulated his saloon...{\r}

1358
02:29:38,585 --> 02:29:42,351
他也知道他走过之后，这些人的笑容就会消失
{\fscx70\fscy70}...he knew that the smiles disappeared
when he passed by.{\r}

1359
02:29:43,457 --> 02:29:45,288
他收到很多很多恶意信件
{\fscx70\fscy70}He received so many menacing letters...{\r}

1360
02:29:45,459 --> 02:29:48,895
到最后他读的时候除了好奇，就没有别的反应了
{\fscx70\fscy70}...that he could read them
without any reaction except curiosity.{\r}

1361
02:29:52,699 --> 02:29:57,500
他整天呆在屋里，翻着扑克牌
{\fscx70\fscy70}He kept to his apartment all day,
flipping over playing cards...{\r}

1362
02:29:59,006 --> 02:30:03,500
在每张K和J牌里注视自己的命运
{\fscx70\fscy70}...looking at his destiny
in every king and jack.{\r}

1363
02:30:07,714 --> 02:30:12,014
8号下午1点，爱德华・奥凯利来了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Edward O'Kelly came up from Bachelor
at 1 p.m. On the 8th.{\r}

1364
02:30:13,487 --> 02:30:17,423
他没有什么大计，没有策略
{\fscx70\fscy70}He had no grand scheme, no strategy...{\r}

1365
02:30:17,591 --> 02:30:19,991
没有和警方订任何协议
{\fscx70\fscy70}...no agreement with higher authorities...{\r}

1366
02:30:20,160 --> 02:30:22,924
心里只是暗暗期待着荣誉
{\fscx70\fscy70}...nothing beyond
a vague longing for glory...{\r}

1367
02:30:23,997 --> 02:30:28,263
和向罗伯特・福特报复的心情
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and a generalized wish
for revenge against Robert Ford.{\r}

1368
02:30:36,043 --> 02:30:39,308
- 昨晚怎样？
- 不坏
{\fscx70\fscy70}- How'd it go last night?
- Not so bad.{\r}

1369
02:30:42,549 --> 02:30:43,948
另一支
{\fscx70\fscy70}The other one.{\r}

1370
02:30:46,453 --> 02:30:49,217
爱德华・奥凯利将因二级谋杀
{\fscx70\fscy70}Edward O'Kelly would be ordered
to serve a life sentence...{\r}

1371
02:30:49,389 --> 02:30:52,290
在科罗拉多惩戒所被判终身监禁
{\fscx70\fscy70}...in the Colorado Penitentiary
for second-degree murder.{\r}

1372
02:30:52,459 --> 02:30:55,223
最终，超过7000人签名
{\fscx70\fscy70}Over 7000 signatures
would eventually be gathered...{\r}

1373
02:30:55,395 --> 02:30:57,659
请求释放奥凯利
{\fscx70\fscy70}...on a petition asking for
O'Kelly's release...{\r}

1374
02:30:57,831 --> 02:31:02,825
1902年，州长詹姆斯・B・奥曼将其释放
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and in 1902, Governor James B. Orman
would pardon the man.{\r}

1375
02:31:03,437 --> 02:31:07,840
你不应该戴那个领带夹的，蛋白石不吉祥
{\fscx70\fscy70}You shouldn't be wearing that stickpin
again there, Bob. Opals are unlucky.{\r}

1376
02:31:09,276 --> 02:31:13,474
我运气本身也不好
蛋白石可能还能给我转运呢
{\fscx70\fscy70}My luck's not very good as it is. I don't
think an opal's gonna change that much.{\r}

1377
02:31:14,414 --> 02:31:15,847
我听到了
{\fscx70\fscy70}I hear you.{\r}

1378
02:31:29,429 --> 02:31:31,294
没有人会给鲍勃念颂词
{\fscx70\fscy70}There would be no eulogies for Bob...{\r}

1379
02:31:32,999 --> 02:31:37,095
杂货店也不会卖他遗体的照片
{\fscx70\fscy70}...no photographs of his body
would be sold in sundries stores...{\r}

1380
02:31:37,804 --> 02:31:42,173
没有人会在雨天涌到街上去看他的葬礼行列
{\fscx70\fscy70}...no people would crowd the streets
in the rain to see his funeral cortege...{\r}

1381
02:31:43,910 --> 02:31:46,879
没人会给他写传记
